# Prisma & Database Conventions

## Setup
- Schema lives at `prisma/schema.prisma`
- Singleton client in `src/lib/db.ts` — never create a second Prisma client
- Always import from `@/lib/db` — never import from generated client directly
- Database: PostgreSQL on Railway

## Migrations
- Run `pnpm prisma migrate dev --name description-of-change` for local dev
- Run `pnpm prisma generate` after any schema change
- Never modify migration files after they've been applied

## Schema Conventions
- Model names: `PascalCase` singular (e.g. `Project`, `FactSheet`, `Script`, `Storyboard`)
- Field names: `camelCase` (e.g. `userId`, `factSheetId`, `pipelineRunId`)
- Use `cuid()` for all IDs
- Always add `@@index` on foreign key fields and frequently queried fields
- JSON fields use Prisma `Json` type — used for agent input/output payloads
- Enums: `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE` values (e.g. `PENDING`, `PROCESSING`, `COMPLETED`, `FAILED`)
- Timestamps: `createdAt` with `@default(now())`, `updatedAt` with `@updatedAt`

## Query Patterns
- Always scope user-owned data to `userId` in `where` clauses
- Use `findFirst` with `where: { id, userId }` instead of `findUnique` when enforcing ownership
- Use `deleteMany` with `where: { id, userId }` for ownership-scoped deletes

## Forbidden
- Never write raw SQL unless Prisma cannot handle the query — explain why in a comment
- Never store secrets or API keys in the database
- Never commit generated Prisma client files independently — they are auto-generated
